function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "+100",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 500,
        font_size      = 300,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Left-click to increment your score marker, right-click to increment the city score marker. This button replaces the score marker and the city discs."
    }

    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    local marker

    if alt_click then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('6bff57')
    elseif color == "Green" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('fc3802')
    elseif color == "Yellow" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('e0fb49')
    elseif color == "Red" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('0d8495')
    elseif color == "Blue" then
        mark = getObjectFromGUID('eb4ccb')
    else
        return
    end

    marker.call("increment")
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Tile
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    local co = -0.844 -- column offset
    local cs = 0.3565 -- column scale
    local bs = 0.0526 -- button offset
    local ro = -0.576 -- row offset
    local rs = 0.3565 -- row scale
    local index = 0
    for c = 0,4 do
        for r = 0,4 do
            for b=0,5 do
                -- skip the city service marker
                if not (c == 2 and r == 2 and b == 0) then
                    local button = {
                        width = 20,
                        height = 20,
                        color = {0, 0, 0, 0},
                        hover_color = {0, 0, 0, 0.7},
                        press_color = {0, 0, 0, 0},
                        function_owner = self,
                        click_function = "button"..index,
                        position = {x = co + (c * cs) + (b * bs), y = 0.1, z = ro + (r * rs)},
                        cube = nil, -- the cube object that's placed on this token
                        token = nil, -- the score token object moved by the button on this cube
                        cube_color = nil, -- the color of the cube on this button
                    }

                    self.createButton(button)
                    -- I don't know why current_index is needed, but it has something to do with upvalues
                    -- 'index' is already a local variable, so I don't know why we need another one
                    -- Why don't we need a copy of 'button'?
                    local current_index = b
                    local func = function(obj, player, alt_click)
                        buttonClicked(obj, player, alt_click, current_index, button)
                    end
                    self.setVar("button"..index, func)
                    index = index + 1
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

scoreToken = {
--          green     red       yellow    blue
    [0] = {'0de0a6', '3322fd', '289467', '98c6fd'}, -- water
    [1] = {'ed27ad', '5eb69a', '3d5d30', '71aaaf'}, -- food
    [2] = {'5808d7', '554ff6', 'e6b3dc', 'f14de0'}, -- religion
    [3] = {'f14de0', '881675', 'c8c173', '946adc'}, -- defense
    [4] = {'40acb1', '8a73ef', '212edc', 'b6ccbc'}, -- commerce
    [5] = {'7f1cbf', '204a31', '55a0b9', 'abe989'}, -- entertainment
}

function buttonClicked(board, player, alt_click, index, button)
    local token
    local cubeBag
    local score

    if button.cube then
        -- only allow a player to remove his own cubes
        if button.cube_color ~= player then
            return
        end
        token = button.token
        score = token.getVar("score") - 1

        destroyObject(button.cube)
        button.cube = nil
        button.token = nil
    else
        if player == "Red" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("551726")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][2])
        elseif player == "Green" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("c9ae8b")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][1])
        elseif player == "Blue" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("97bcca")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][4])
        elseif player == "Yellow" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("fd6678")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][3])
        else
            return
        end

        score = token.getVar("score") + 1

        -- We have to invert the X-axis for some log(button)
        local buttonPos = {-button.position.x, button.position.y, button.position.z}
        local params = {
            smooth = false,
            position = board.positionToWorld(buttonPos),
        }
        button.cube = cubeBag.takeObject(params) -- take the cube from the cube Bag
        button.cube.interactable = false
        button.token = token
        button.cube_color = player
    end

    token.setVar("score", score)
    if score > 14 then
        score = 14
    end

    local tokenPos = token.getPosition()
    tokenPos.x = -0.9011 + 1.4 * score
    tokenPos.y = 2
    token.setPosition(tokenPos)
end

function onLoad()
    children = self.getChildren()[1].getChildren()[1].getChildren()
    children[1].getComponents()[1].set('localScale', {0.8,2,1}) -- next page    
    children[2].getComponents()[1].set('localScale', {0.8,2,1}) -- prev page
    children[3].getComponents()[1].set('localScale', {1,0.5,1}) -- pop out
    children[1].getComponents()[1].set('localPosition', {340, 0, 0})
    children[2].getComponents()[1].set('localPosition', {-340, 0, 0})
end
